10. Limitations

Several limitations should be considered:

The dataset may be synthetic or limited in size.
Fraud patterns evolve over time, potentially reducing model performance.
The model should not be used as the sole basis for approving or rejecting transactions.
Regular retraining and monitoring are required to maintain effectiveness.

11. Recommendations

The selected model demonstrated strong performance in identifying suspicious transactions and is suitable as a decision-support tool for fraud analysts.

To improve future performance, the following enhancements are recommended:

Collect additional real-world transaction data.
Evaluate advanced algorithms such as XGBoost or LightGBM.
Incorporate explainable AI techniques such as SHAP values.
Monitor model performance for concept drift.
Deploy the model using a production-ready API such as FastAPI.
